    "waitForText": {
      "id": "lf_help_title",
      "value": "Help"
    }
  },
  {
    "waitForText": {
      "id": "lf_help_0",
      "value": "This tool compares a term loan and lease to obtain business equipment. To compare the value of payments over time for the lease-or-loan option, the calculator shows payments in present value."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_1",
      "value": "A term loan helps you to buy the equipment. While your business pays all expenses, it realizes substantial tax savings from these expenses. However, loan financing crimps your cash flows: a down payment is a large initial expenditure, and your monthly payments are larger to include repayment of loan principal. If your business is a young enterprise, you may not have the level of cash necessary to sustain high debt payments."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_2",
      "value": "A lease lets you obtain business equipment at a cost that is generally less than loan financing. Using an operating lease, your monthly lease payments will be lower than loan payments. You also avoid a down payment. Instead, you pay a security deposit that is much smaller than a down payment on a purchase. When the lease term expires, you have more flexibility than with a loan. You can renew the lease, exercise a purchase option, or, in most cases, walk away. Leasing may also be advantageous if the equipment becomes obsolete quickly."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_3",
      "value": "Key assumptions of this tool include:"
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_4",
      "value": "Depreciation. The calculator uses the double-declining balance ( DDB ) method and MACRS to depreciate equipment. It switches to straight-line depreciation in the year that depreciation expense under that method is greater. The half-year convention is used to calculate depreciation expense for the first year, regardless of purchase date."
    }
  },
  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf_help_5",
      "value": "If the original lease term is shorter than the useful life of the equipment, it is assumed that you exercise the purchase option at the end of the lease term."
    }
  },
